    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-02-06T19:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-02-06T19:00:00-05:00" n="483"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d483">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 800.24/49a</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_SWG1" type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sharp</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-02-06T19:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">February 6, 1918, 7 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3148. Your 3082, January 23, 3 p.m., and 3143, February 4, 6 p.m.<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d483fn1">The latter not printed.</note> Secretary of War has been
                    consulted and he approves Department’s instruction to you to confer with
                        <persName corresp="#p_PGJJ1">General Pershing</persName> and to request him
                    to assign one of his staff to attend conference mentioned. Report whom <persName
                        corresp="#p_PGJJ1">General Pershing</persName> designates.<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d483fn2">See telegram No. 3530 from the Ambassador in France, Apr.
                        5, <hi rend="italic">post</hi>, <ref target="#pg_562">p. 562</ref>.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_PFL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
